Class InvalidDataException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • recipeTool.InvalidDataException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class InvalidDataException
extends java.lang.Exception
    This exception is thrown, when invalid, or malformed data is encountered.
    If constructed using a String as parameter, this implementation will precede that string with:
    "Data received from the database is invalid."
    and then append the string as a message.
    Author:
    Ville Salmela

    • Method Detail

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        This method will create a string with information about the exception.
        It consists of the exception class name, predefined message and a customizable message.
        If the customizable message is not specified when instantiating the exception, only the class name is included.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Throwable
        Returns:
        if the Throwable.getLocalizedMessage() is null: exception class name.
        if the Throwable.getLocalizedMessage() is not null: "Data received from the database is invalid.\n" + message
